<ns4132:section xmlns:ns4132="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xml:id="resources.information.technologies.java.j2se.swing.developingSwingInterfaces.editorSkeleton.popupMenus">
    <ns4133:title xmlns:ns4133="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Pop-up Menus</ns4133:title>
    <ns4134:para xmlns:ns4134="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Pop-up menus are usually triggered by mouse events (e.g. mouse right-button click events).
        or this purpose we define an inner class, <ns4135:literal xmlns:ns4135="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">MouseCickListener</ns4135:literal> and each
        editor pane (each internal frame) ahs its own mouse click listener. To make the application
        platform independent, we do not check for mouse right-button click events, but ask the event
        whether it is a pop-up trigger via</ns4134:para>
    <ns4136:para xmlns:ns4136="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
        <ns4137:programlisting xmlns:ns4137="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
         if (event.isPopupTrigger())
        </ns4137:programlisting>
    </ns4136:para>
